32:18.347 --> 32:21.514
(birds chirping)

32:23.180 --> 32:26.263
(dog barking)

32:26.347 --> 32:29.514
(chirping continues)

32:30.472 --> 32:32.222
Jonathan:
Are you tired of walking?

32:32.305 --> 32:34.138
-Fraser: No, not really.
Are you?
-No, I say it

32:34.222 --> 32:37.514
because you don't exactly
seem like the athletic type.

32:39.847 --> 32:41.764
Oh, I was kidding!

32:41.847 --> 32:44.847
You are so sensitive.

32:44.931 --> 32:46.972
What is this place?
Why'd you bring me here?

32:47.055 --> 32:50.764
Some of the most violent battles
in history took place in here.

32:50.847 --> 32:54.514
Young men were dying like
flies into those trenches,

32:54.597 --> 32:57.222
and it would go on
for days on end.

32:58.138 --> 32:59.597
(sheep baaing)

32:59.681 --> 33:01.889
Did the Nazis
drop the bombs?

33:01.972 --> 33:04.430
This was World War I,
smart boy.

33:04.514 --> 33:06.514
(giggles) No Nazis?

33:06.597 --> 33:08.347
-(sucks teeth)
-What's that?

33:09.389 --> 33:10.597
SACRARIO.

33:11.889 --> 33:13.138
What is SACRARIO?

33:13.222 --> 33:16.180
One of the biggest
Clubs 27 on Earth.

33:16.263 --> 33:19.222
There's about 50,000
dead men in there,

33:19.305 --> 33:22.013
and over 30,000
are MILITI IGNOTI.

33:23.222 --> 33:26.347
-What is MILITI IGNOTI?
-Unknown soldiers.

33:26.430 --> 33:28.806
After the explosions,
the men's bodies

33:28.889 --> 33:31.889
were so mangled up,
they couldn't tell them apart.

33:31.972 --> 33:33.389
-Fraser: Fuck.
-Jonathan: Yeah.

33:34.138 --> 33:35.013
Fraser:
Shit.

33:35.097 --> 33:38.305
That's why they
buried them together.

33:38.389 --> 33:40.138
Why on Earth would
you bring me here?

33:40.222 --> 33:43.514
(laughs) Why not? Look around.

33:43.597 --> 33:45.138
It's beautiful.

33:45.222 --> 33:46.806
What are you talking about?
50,000 dead men?

33:46.889 --> 33:49.305
-Mm-hmm.
-I mean, that's kinda...

33:49.389 --> 33:51.847
unidyllic--
Unusual for a first date.
I mean, for a first--

33:51.931 --> 33:55.097
-for a first whatever.
-First whatever.

34:01.430 --> 34:02.806
Jonathan:
Ah!

34:04.138 --> 34:07.514
-(cowbell ringing)
-So you like nature.

34:07.597 --> 34:09.847
Uh, yeah.
I mean, I like it a lot.

34:09.931 --> 34:12.347
I like, uh, um...

34:12.430 --> 34:14.514
I just don't like
spiders or insects

34:14.597 --> 34:16.180
or green things.

34:16.263 --> 34:18.472
(sheep baaing)

34:25.222 --> 34:27.681
(laughter)

34:33.097 --> 34:35.222
-(laughing)
-Jonathan: Go!

34:35.305 --> 34:37.472
-(sheep baaing)

34:39.472 --> 34:40.972
-(laughing)
-(dog barking)

34:41.055 --> 34:43.180
(baaing continues)

34:49.305 --> 34:50.597
Don't you have to go?

34:50.681 --> 34:53.180
Uh, no, not right now.
Thank you.

34:53.263 --> 34:55.347
(urinating)

34:57.263 --> 34:59.430
(baaing continues)

35:02.889 --> 35:05.764
(dog barking)

35:05.847 --> 35:09.138
You have no idea the relief
you're missing out on.

35:21.681 --> 35:23.555
(urinating)

35:23.639 --> 35:26.847
-Watch out for
the green things. (laughs)
-(laughing)

35:29.347 --> 35:31.681
-(cowbell ringing)
-(laughing)

35:33.847 --> 35:35.013
(laughs)

35:36.639 --> 35:39.222
-Are you sure you can stay?
-Yes! Of course!

35:39.305 --> 35:41.722
-Do you want me to
call your mother?
-No.

35:41.806 --> 35:43.472
No, no, no, it's alright.

35:43.555 --> 35:45.764
(restaurant chatter)

35:45.847 --> 35:48.222
-(waitress speaking Italian)
-(Jonathan speaking Italian)

35:49.555 --> 35:51.222
-Uh, leave it, leave it.
-Ah, okay.

35:58.055 --> 35:59.347
Do you want a Coke?

35:59.430 --> 36:01.722
-No, wine would be great.
-Okay.

36:01.806 --> 36:04.180
Wine would be great.

36:04.263 --> 36:05.514
Isn't it beautiful here?

36:05.597 --> 36:07.597
It's beautiful!
It is, yeah.

36:07.681 --> 36:10.389
(clears throat)
It's beautiful.

36:11.222 --> 36:12.222
(door shuts)

36:14.889 --> 36:17.806
-Be-a-utiful.
-(tapping table)

36:17.889 --> 36:19.722
(drumming)

36:22.472 --> 36:23.931
(Fraser giggles)

36:33.597 --> 36:34.931
(pouring)

36:40.222 --> 36:42.180
-To this day we're
spending together.
-(clink)

36:42.263 --> 36:44.597
To meeting you, and then
seeing you at the theater,

36:44.681 --> 36:47.347
-and being able to know you--
-Woo! Whoa!

36:47.430 --> 36:49.305
-(woman laughing)
-There she is!

36:50.430 --> 36:52.764
Marta, meet Fraser.

36:53.597 --> 36:55.055
-Marta: Hi.
-Fraser,

36:55.138 --> 36:57.389
-meet my friend.
-Nice to meet you.

36:57.472 --> 36:59.430
-(microphone feedback)
-Fraser: Nice to meet you.

36:59.514 --> 37:00.430
Marta.

37:00.514 --> 37:02.013
I've heard so much about you.

37:02.097 --> 37:03.347
Yeah. (laughs)

37:03.430 --> 37:06.013
Are you really as brilliant
as Jonathan says?

37:11.430 --> 37:13.180
Brilliant?

37:13.263 --> 37:15.764
-(energetic music playing)
-Brilliant.

37:15.847 --> 37:16.764
Um...

37:16.847 --> 37:18.722
-Jonathan: Oh my God.
-I'm just strange.

37:18.806 --> 37:20.305
(Marta laughing)

37:23.597 --> 37:25.389
(music continues)

37:25.472 --> 37:27.430
-You love this song!
-But they are not singing!

37:27.514 --> 37:31.013
-They are, like,
ruining it right now. Ugh!
-(Marta laughs)

37:32.138 --> 37:35.514
-(Marta laughing)
-(timid singing in Italian)

37:35.597 --> 37:39.347
Jonathan:
